{[#]} 12... e5 {With his last move Black revealed his intentions to place his
knight on d4. In such cases, it makes sense to place the bishop on e3 instead
of the queen. The queen has no proper square to go to and therefore it makes
sense to exchange queens!} 13. Qg5 $1 Qxg5 (13... f6 14. Qh4 $14 {[%csl Rg7]})
14. Bxg5 {[%csl Rd6][%cal Gg5e3] Black has to act fast before White moves his
bishop to e3 which would lead to a passive position for Black.} Nd4 {Black is
trying to muddy the waters} 15. Nxd4 (15. Bf1 $5 f6 16. Be3 Nc2 17. Rxd6 Nxe4
18. Nxe4 Nxa1 19. Rd2 $44 {[%cal Ge4d6]}) 15... exd4 16. Nd5 {[%cal Rg5e7]}
Nxe4 (16... f6 17. Bf4 $18 {[%csl Rd4,Rd6]}) 17. Be7 Re8 18. Bf3 Be6 (18... Bf5
19. Bxe4 Bxe4 20. Nf6+ Bxf6 21. Bxf6 {with a slight pull for Work.}) 19. Nc7
Rxe7 20. Nxa8 Bxc4 (20... Nc5 21. Nb6 $14) 21. Rac1 (21. Nb6 {was stronger} Bb5
22. Nc8 Re6 23. Bxe4 Rxe4 24. Nxd6 $16) 21... d5 22. Nb6 {White somehow
managed to win.} Bh6 23. b3 Re6 24. bxc4 Bxc1 25. Nxd5 Bg5 26. Rxd4 Nd2 27. h4
Nxf3+ 28. gxf3 Bd8 29. h5 gxh5 30. Nf4 Re1+ 31. Kg2 Be7 32. Rd7 b5 33. c5 Kf8
34. c6 Ke8 35. Nxh5 Rc1 36. Ng7+ Kf8 37. Nf5 Bf6 38. Rd6 Be7 39. Rd7 Bg5 40. f4
Bf6 41. c7 Ke8 42. Rd6 Be7 43. Ng7+ Kf8 44. Rd8+ Kxg7 45. c8=Q Rxc8 46. Rxc8 a5
47. Ra8 a4 48. Ra5 a3 49. Rxb5 Kg6 50. Rb6+ f6 51. Kf3 h5 52. Ke4 h4 53. Kf3 h3
54. Rb8 Bd6 55. Rh8 {1-0 (55) Sjugirov,S (2643)-Gabrielian,A (2558) Izhevsk
2014} *

