1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Bb5 Bd7 6. Qd3 Nf6 (6... Nb4 7.
Bxd7+ Qxd7 8. Qe2 g6 (8... Nf6 9. O-O e6 10. Rd1 Qc6 11. Nc3 Be7 12. a3 Na6 13.
Nd4 Qc8 14. Ndb5 $18 {1-0 (36) Cadilhac,I (2286)-Ozgur,T (2056) Manavgat TUR
2018}) 9. O-O Bg7 10. c3 Nc6 11. c4 Nf6 12. h3 O-O 13. Nc3 $14 {[%csl Gc4,Ge4]
1-0 (43) Karjakin,S (2763)-Nakamura,H (2787) Moscow RUS 2018}) (6... a6 7. Bxc6
Bxc6 8. c4 Nf6 (8... b5 9. Nc3 bxc4 10. Qxc4 Qc8 11. Nd4 Bd7 12. Qd3 e6 13. Bg5
Qc5 14. Be3 Qh5 15. f3 Qh4+ 16. g3 Qd8 17. O-O-O $16 {1/2-1/2 (52) Aravindh
Chithambaram Vr (2581)-Fedoseev,V (2707) Abu Dhabi UAE 2018}) 9. Nc3 e6 10. O-O
Be7 {transposes}) (6... g6 7. c4 Bg7 8. Nc3 {with typical play as in the main
line}) (6... Rc8 7. c4 {The play more or less transposes to the main line.}) 7.
c4 g6 (7... e6 8. Nc3 Be7 (8... a6 9. Bxc6 Bxc6 10. O-O Be7 11. Nd4 Rc8 12.
Nxc6 Rxc6 13. Ne2 O-O 14. Nd4 Rc8 15. b3 $14 {[%csl Gb3,Gc4,Ge4] 1-0 (44)
Macieja,B (2630)-Gonzalez Zamora,J (2527) Puebla 2013}) 9. O-O O-O 10. Rd1 a6
11. Bxc6 Bxc6 12. Nd4 Rc8 13. b3 Qa5 14. Bb2 $14 {1-0 (31) Perelshteyn,E (2505)
-Danelia, M (2256) Dallas 2016}) 8. Nc3 Bg7 9. O-O O-O 10. h3 {A useful move
in such positions.} a6 (10... Rc8 11. Be3 Nb4 (11... a6 12. Bxc6 Bxc6 (12...
Rxc6 13. Rac1 Qa5 14. Bd2 Qb6 15. b3 Rfc8 16. Rfe1 $14 {0-1 (53) Nemcova,K 
(2314)-Nakar, E (2419) Pardubice CZE 2014}) 13. Nd4 e6 (13... Bd7 14. b3 Qa5
15. a4 Rfe8 16. Rac1 Bc6 17. Rfd1 $14 {1/2-1/2 (59) Castellanos Rodriguez,R 
(2480)-Lalic,B (2451) Cesenatico ITA 2015}) (13... Re8 14. Rac1 e6 15. Rfd1 Qe7
16. b3 Red8 17. Nxc6 Rxc6 18. Bg5 $14 {1-0 (51) Halak,M (2186)-Vaclavicek,L 
(2067) Liberec CZE 2017}) 14. Rfd1 Qe7 15. Nxc6 Rxc6 16. Bf4 Ne8 17. Rac1 $14 {
1-0 (35) Zhang Zhong (2633)-Nguyen Anh Dung (2478) Ho Chi Minh City VIE 2016})
(11... Be6 12. b3 Nd7 13. Qd2 f6 14. Rad1 $14 {1-0 (27) Macieja,B (2612)
-Nasuta,G (2237) Warsaw POL 2011}) (11... Ne8 12. Rac1 b6 13. Rfd1 Ne5 14. Nxe5
Bxe5 15. b3 $16 {1-0 (35) Nestorovic,N (2434)-Goossens,H (2092)
Cappelle-la-Grande FRA 2014}) 12. Qe2 a6 13. Bxd7 Nxd7 14. Rac1 Bxc3 (14... Qc7
15. b3 $14 {1-0 (94) Andreikin,D (2736)-Kryakvin,D (2554) Sochi RUS 2016}) 15.
Rxc3 Nxa2 16. Rb3 Nc5 17. Bxc5 dxc5 18. Rxb7 Rc7 19. Rxc7 Qxc7 20. Qd2 $1 {
[%cal Gd2h6,Gf1d1]} Nb4 21. Rd1 Nc6 22. Qh6 f6 23. Qe3 $14 {1-0 (50) Macieja,B
(2583)-Margvelashvili,G (2555) Santa Clara USA 2014}) (10... Nb4 11. Qe2 a6 12.
Bxd7 Nxd7 13. Bd2 Rc8 14. Rfd1 Re8 15. Rac1 Nc6 16. Be1 Nc5 17. b3 $14 {
1-0 (40) Alekseev,E (2665) -Khismatullin,D (2650) Sochi RUS 2015}) (10... Ne8
11. Be3 Nc7 (11... f5 12. exf5 Bxf5 13. Qe2 Nc7 14. Rad1 Qd7 15. Nd5 e5 16.
Nxc7 Qxc7 17. c5 d5 18. Rxd5 Be4 19. Bxc6 Qxc6 20. Rd6 $18 {1-0 (36) Chigaev,M
(2526)-Polok,K (2228) Krakow POL 2015}) 12. Bxc6 Bxc6 (12... bxc6 13. Rad1 Qb8
14. b3 Rd8 15. Bg5 f6 16. Be3 $14 {1/2-1/2 (64) Alekseev,E (2636)-Bodnaruk,A 
(2465) St Petersburg RUS 2016}) 13. Bd4 Ne6 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. b4 f6 16. Nd5 $14
{1-0 (30) Sjugirov,S (2663) -Pridorozhni,A (2567) Khanty-Mansiysk RUS 2018})
11. Bxc6 Bxc6 12. Nd4 {[%csl Gc4,Ge4] We immediately centralize our knight so
that we can capture on c6 whenever necessary.} Nd7 {[%cal Gd7c5,Gc5e6] Black
has to challenge the knight on d4 by playing Nc5-e6. In the process he also
improves the scope of his Bg7.} 13. Be3 Rc8 14. Rac1 {We generally place our
queenside rook on c1 and the kingside rook on d1} Nc5 (14... Qa5 15. b3 Rfd8
16. Qd2 {[%cal Ge3h6,Yd2a5,Rc3d5] White can play Bh6 at the appropriate moment
and also keeps an eye on the e1-a5 diagonal.} e6 17. Rfd1 Nf6 18. f3 Be8 19. a4
{[%csl Ga4,Gb3,Rb5,Gc4]} Nd7 20. Kh1 Ne5 21. Bh6 Bxh6 22. Qxh6 Nc6 23. Nde2 $14
{1-0 (78) Alekseev,E (2616) -Karjakin,S (2760) Riyadh KSA 2017}) (14... e6 15.
Rfd1 Nc5 16. Qc2 Qh4 17. f3 Be5 18. b4 Nd7 19. b5 axb5 20. cxb5 Bxd4 21. Rxd4
Bxb5 22. Qd2 Bc6 23. Bg5 $16 {1-0 (37) Alekseev,E (2636)-Matinian,N (2488) St
Petersburg RUS 2016}) 15. Qc2 Ne6 (15... Bd7 16. Rfd1 b5 17. cxb5 axb5 18.
Ndxb5 Qa5 19. Nd5 Qxb5 20. Nxe7+ Kh8 21. Nxc8 Rxc8 22. Rxd6 $16 {1-0 (47)
Hracek,Z (2646)-Kriebel,T (2428) Slovakia SVK 2014}) (15... Qe8 16. b3 {
The knight on d4 is in no way inferior to the bishop on c6 and hence there is
no need to capture on c6 immediately.} (16. Nxc6 Rxc6 17. b4 Nd7 $11 {1/2-1/2 
(42) Nitin, S (2404)-Nguyen Huynh Minh Huy (2496) Al-Ain UAE 2015})) 16. Qd2 (
16. Nxe6 fxe6 $132 {[%cal Gc6h1,Gg7a1,Yb7b5] In general we refrain from this
capture as it offers enough counterplay for Black ½-½ (69) Gara,A (2370)
-Groszpeter, A (2437) Hungary HUN 2018}) 16... Nxd4 (16... Qa5 17. Rfd1 Qe5 (
17... Rfe8 {[%csl Ge7][%cal Ge8e7] Nice prophylaxis as he defends the e7 pawn
in advance} 18. a3 Bd7 19. b4 $1 $146 {and if} (19. Nb3 Qh5 $11 {1/2-1/2 (41)
Jurcik, M (2492)-Markos, J (2592) Banska Stiavnica SVK 2015}) 19... Qxa3 20. Nd5
{[%csl Ra3][%cal Gd5b6,Gc1a1]} Nxd4 21. Bxd4 Bxd4 22. Qxd4 Be6 23. Nb6 $36 {
[%csl Gb6] A powerful knight on b6 and Black's misplaced queen offer White a
great compensation.}) 18. Nf3 $1 Qh5 19. Nd5 Rfe8 20. Re1 Nc5 21. Bg5 $16 {
1-0 (82) Kokarev,D (2598)-Sarana,A (2618) Khanty-Mansiysk RUS 2018}) (16... Qe8
17. Rfe1 Nxd4 18. Bxd4 b5 19. Bxg7 Kxg7 20. Qd4+ Kg8 21. cxb5 (21. Qb6 $14 {
1-0 (45) Alekseev,E (2620)-Bagautdinov,I Kazan RUS 2018}) 21... axb5 22. e5 {
was probably stronger}) 17. Bxd4 Bxd4 (17... f5 $6 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. exf5 Rxf5
20. Rfe1 $14 Qc7 21. Nd5 {1-0 (21) Idani,P (2552)-Soozankar,A (2302) Sareyn
IRI 2017}) 18. Qxd4 Qa5 {[%csl Gc4,Rc6,Ge4][%cal Gf1e1,Ge1d1] This is what
Black should probably do. Black's bishop is standing better on c6 and he
should capture the knight whenever White plays Nd5, thus reaching a major
piece ending with equal chances. Till then he has to just sit and wait. On the
contrary, White improves his position to the maximum and waits for the right
opportunity to enter a better version of a major piece ending by playing Nd5.
He also has ideas like h4 to push the h-pawn even further to create attacking
chances. In general, the position is fairly balanced.} *

