{[#] Black's last move was Nf6-d7 with the obvious intention to play Nc5 in
order to attack the weak b3 pawn. How should White continue?} 20. Qd3 $1 {
[%cal Gd3c2] A multi-purpose move as White not only intends to defend the
b3-pawn, but also to move the queen away from the d-file since it is
preferable to place the queen behind the rook and not in front of it!} Nc5 21.
Qc2 Qc7 {White has stabilized the queenside. What should White do now?} 22. h4
$1 $14 {White increases the space advantage on the kingside as well.} *

